value.title: Trump touted that he and McConnell 'have broken every record' with judicial appointments: report
value.excerpt: President Trump touted to journalist Bob Woodward that he and Senate Majority Leader Mitch McConnell, R-Ky., “have broken every record” when it comes to judicial appointments.

value.title: Jeff Zucker Helped Create Donald Trump. That Show May Be Ending.

value.excerpt: The woman was taken into custody by U.S. Customs and Border Protection officers at the Peace Bridge border crossing near Buffalo, authorities said.

value.title: Virus Pulls Down Trump, Poll Shows, and G.O.P. Senators Suffer With Him
value.excerpt: A New York Times/Siena College survey showed Joe Biden leading President Trump by wide margins in Maine and Arizona, and effectively tied in North Carolina. Susan Collins trailed her Democratic rival in Maine’s Senate race.

value.title: Biden holds sizable lead over Trump among Latino voters in NBC/WSJ/Telemundo poll
value.excerpt: The 62 percent to 26 percent margin is less of an advantage than Hillary Clinton held at this point of the race in 2016.

value.title: Biden says 200 million people have died from COVID-19 as campaign gaffes continue
value.excerpt: 2020 presidential candidate Joe Biden had another major public gaffe on Sunday when he said an estimated 200 million people have already died from the coronavirus, even though the number of American casualties is closer to 200,000.

value.title: Pelosi on possible second Trump impeachment in lame duck session — ‘We have our options’
value.excerpt: House Speaker Nancy Pelosi on Sunday did not rule out impeaching President Trump or Attorney General William Barr if the Senate tries to push through a Supreme Court nomination during a lame-duck session if Joe Biden wins the November election.

value.title: Chuck Todd Presses HHS Sec. Azar on Trump Covid Messaging: Who Should Americans Be Listening to on Masks?
value.excerpt: Chuck Todd pressed HHS Secretary Alex Azar on Meet the Press Sunday over President Donald Trump's public health messaging being at odds with top officials like the head of the CDC.

value.title: Trump takes swipe at Murkowski after she opposes Senate taking up SCOTUS confirmation
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump eyed a tweet earlier Sunday morning from the Alaska Chamber which promoted an event slated for next week featuring Alaska Sen. Lisa Murkowski.

value.title: Herschel Walker reveals ‘truth’ about BLM, Trump: 'I'm going to fight for' America
value.excerpt: Former NFL player Herschel Walker urged BLM supporters to think about what they're promoting and defended President Trump's character.

value.title: Biden implores key Republicans: 'Follow your conscience' on Ginsburg replacement
value.excerpt: The Democratic nominee accused McConnell and Trump of performing "an exercise in raw political power" that the nation will not stand for.

value.title: Watch Live: Joe Biden Speaks On Supreme Court Vacancy In Philadelphia
value.excerpt: Former Vice President Joe Biden is scheduled to deliver remarks on the vacancy left by the death of Supreme Court Justice Ruth Bader Ginsburg from Philadelphia on Sunday afternoon.

value.title: Biden to make health care push as Supreme Court vacancy fight looms
value.excerpt: Democratic presidential nominee Joe Biden intends to make a push on health care in the wake of Supreme Court Justice Ruth Bader Ginsburg's death as a political fight over the Supreme Court vacancy is already underway.

value.title: Maya Rudolph wins Emmy as Kamala Harris; Jason Bateman given Ron Cephas Jones' award
value.excerpt: Maya Rudolph won a Creative Arts Emmy for her "SNL" role as Kamala Harris, and a ceremony gaffe crowned Jason Bateman instead of Ron Cephas Jones.

value.title: GOP's Scott, Baker don't want Trump to fill Supreme Court vacancy before election
value.excerpt: "The Supreme Court is too important to rush and must be removed from partisan political infighting," Gov. Charlie Baker wrote.

value.title: Hillary Clinton says McConnell, Trump move to confirm Ginsburg successor shows 'lust for power'
value.excerpt: The former Democratic president and former Democratic presidential nominee weighed in on the fight over the seat of the late Justice Ruth Bader Ginsburg

value.title: Trump tells supporters 'you'll never see me again' if he loses to Biden
value.excerpt: Trump made similar remarks in 2016, saying, "I don't think I'm going to lose, but if I do, I don't think you're ever going to see me again."

value.title: Judge delays Trump administration’s restrictions on messaging app WeChat
value.excerpt: In a ruling dated Saturday, a judge in California said the government’s actions would affect users' First Amendment rights as an effective ban on the app removes their platform for communication.

value.title: Bill Clinton: 'Superficially hypocritical' for Trump and Republicans to push to fill Supreme Court vacancy
value.excerpt: Former President Bill Clinton said Sunday it is "superficially hypocritical" for President Donald Trump and Senate Republicans to push to put a new justice on the Supreme Court before the November election.

value.title: Pelosi won't rule out new impeachment to delay SCOTUS vote if Biden wins
value.excerpt: "Well, we have our options," Pelosi told ABC's "This Week." "We have arrows in our quiver that I’m not about to discuss right now."

value.title: Joe Biden headed to Manitowoc Monday for second Wisconsin visit
value.excerpt: Joe Biden’s campaign announced Sunday that the Democratic presidential nominee would be campaigning in Manitowoc, a city of about 32,000 about 80 miles north of Milwaukee.

value.title: Students are in a lose-lose situation during the pandemic, and Trump is to blame
value.excerpt: Trump's leadership during the pandemic has left students stuck between a rock and a hard place. Joe Biden has the skills necessary to succeed.

value.title: Computing pioneers endorse Biden, citing Trump immigration crackdown
value.excerpt: Two dozen award-winning computer scientists, in a rebuke of President Donald Trump’s immigration policies, said Friday that they were endorsing Joe Biden in November’s presidential election.

value.title: Trump remains the underdog as campaign enters final six-week stretch
value.excerpt: This year has felt anything but stable in most aspects of American life, but the presidential campaign of 2020 has been bucking that dynamic and has proven to be remarkably stable for the last several months.
